1
00:01:31,039 --> 00:01:35,990
[Life is a Choice]

2
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:37,820
You kindly saved him.

3
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,310
Why did he hit you?

4
00:01:40,539 --> 00:01:42,620
Well, in the service industry,

5
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:44,110
the customer is always right.

6
00:01:44,110 --> 00:01:46,009
Besides, he was drunk.

7
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:46,940
It was understandable.

8
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:50,830
Huanan, can you quit this job?

9
00:01:51,050 --> 00:01:52,080
How could I?

10
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:54,420
With just the salary from my day job,

11
00:01:55,050 --> 00:01:56,539
it'll take ages before I can marry you.

12
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:58,509
It's fine.

13
00:02:01,710 --> 00:02:04,120
I'm already exhausted from work during the day.

14
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,470
When I get home, I just want to lie down.

15
00:02:05,550 --> 00:02:07,180
And yet you still have to do designated driving.

16
00:02:08,389 --> 00:02:10,389
No, that's too tiring.

17
00:02:10,669 --> 00:02:13,030
It's not tiring. I'm a man, after all.

18
00:02:13,070 --> 00:02:14,540
Isn't it normal for me to work hard?

19
00:02:14,870 --> 00:02:16,430
Besides, a lot of men nowadays

20
00:02:16,430 --> 00:02:18,430
work a full-time job during the day

21
00:02:18,579 --> 00:02:20,250
and take on side jobs at night to make extra money.

22
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,850
[Episode 18]

23
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,310
As long as my wife is happy,

24
00:02:22,950 --> 00:02:24,900
a little hardship is worth it.

25
00:02:25,660 --> 00:02:27,630
[I'm Going to Marry You]

26
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:28,290
How about this?

27
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:30,270
I'll make money with you.

28
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:31,340
I'll do designated driving too.

29
00:02:31,370 --> 00:02:32,850
No, that won't do.

30
00:02:33,210 --> 00:02:34,540
If your mom finds out

31
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,310
her precious daughter is going through such a hardship,

32
00:02:36,380 --> 00:02:38,020
she'll definitely look down on me even more.

33
00:02:38,350 --> 00:02:39,550
Isn't she just looking down on you

34
00:02:39,550 --> 00:02:41,030
because of your job and low income?

35
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:42,150
I'll be just like you.

36
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:42,990
Let's see what she'll say then.

37
00:02:43,010 --> 00:02:44,770
Don't go against your mom.

38
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:47,280
This was my fault.

39
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,579
I was too impulsive.

40
00:02:49,390 --> 00:02:51,390
I shouldn't have let my love for you

41
00:02:51,550 --> 00:02:52,470
and my desire to protect you

42
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:53,570
make me overlook the reality,

43
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:54,090
right?

44
00:02:54,390 --> 00:02:55,990
You're always speaking up for her.

45
00:02:55,990 --> 00:02:57,950
She's never said a single nice word about you.

46
00:02:58,990 --> 00:03:00,910
Well, it was the first time your mom met me.

47
00:03:01,310 --> 00:03:02,790
It's normal that she doesn't know me well.

48
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:05,380
And not everyone

49
00:03:05,410 --> 00:03:07,120
is as lucky as us.

50
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:09,100
We've managed to get back together

51
00:03:09,420 --> 00:03:10,810
and love each other without caring about material conditions.

52
00:03:11,370 --> 00:03:12,370
How many people would envy us?

53
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:14,680
Let me tell you, Nian,

54
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:16,990
there are so many people who hold the belief

55
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,400
that poor couples are miserable.

56
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:21,990
But I'm determined to prove them wrong.

57
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,750
You've worked hard today.

58
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,480
Here, this is for you.

59
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:31,190
Boost some dopamine that makes people happy.

60
00:03:31,950 --> 00:03:33,590
You bought me a cake?

61
00:03:33,610 --> 00:03:35,210
It's so cute.

62
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,140
[The Gu Family's Important Day]

63
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:37,260
It must taste great.

64
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:39,110
I'm glad you like it.

65
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,079
Why did you waste money on this cake?

66
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,680
Well, I work so hard to earn money

67
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,270
just to make you happy.

68
00:03:47,590 --> 00:03:48,670
You must be tired, Huanan.

69
00:03:49,550 --> 00:03:50,790
I'm not that tired.

70
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:52,990
It's just that sometimes,

71
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:54,270
when I'm tired,

72
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:56,510
missing you so much makes it really hard to bear.

73
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:00,350
Nian,

74
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:02,230
trust me.

75
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:04,720
The hardship now is only temporary.

76
00:04:04,990 --> 00:04:07,590
I will definitely find a suitable job.

77
00:04:07,970 --> 00:04:10,170
But you, don't overwork yourself.

78
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:12,980
We're not in the same company anymore,

79
00:04:13,450 --> 00:04:15,090
so I can't always take care of you.

80
00:04:15,290 --> 00:04:17,010
You'll probably have to take care of yourself.

81
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:20,519
And, in the coming period,

82
00:04:20,649 --> 00:04:22,019
I might be quite busy.

83
00:04:23,690 --> 00:04:25,650
We won't be able to see each other like we do now.

84
00:04:26,210 --> 00:04:28,650
Don't worry, I'll work twice as hard.

85
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:30,650
I believe that one day,

86
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,010
I'll make your mom approve of me.

87
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,770
I'm afraid that I'm destined

88
00:04:37,370 --> 00:04:38,409
not to see that day come.

89
00:04:39,380 --> 00:04:40,450
Even if that's the case,

90
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:42,690
I'll crawl my way through

91
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:45,220
to marry you.

92
00:04:46,450 --> 00:04:48,210
Anyway, I won't let you suffer like this.

93
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:49,970
What are you planning to do?

94
00:04:50,030 --> 00:04:51,030
Don't worry about it, okay?

95
00:05:09,290 --> 00:05:10,010
Godmother.

96
00:05:11,410 --> 00:05:13,290
Su, why are you here?

97
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:15,160
I'm here to accompany you to visit Godfather.

98
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:16,530
How did you know

99
00:05:16,530 --> 00:05:18,210
today is Gu's death anniversary?

100
00:05:18,410 --> 00:05:19,490
Gu Nian told me.

101
00:05:19,690 --> 00:05:20,690
We're really busy today,

102
00:05:20,690 --> 00:05:22,170
and she couldn't leave, so she sent me instead.

103
00:05:22,450 --> 00:05:22,850
Godmother.

104
00:05:22,970 --> 00:05:24,350
I'll ride in your car later.

105
00:05:24,370 --> 00:05:25,650
I came here on my motorcycle today.

106
00:05:26,450 --> 00:05:28,290
Then let's take your motorcycle.

107
00:05:28,610 --> 00:05:30,170
You want to go there by motorcycle?

108
00:05:30,890 --> 00:05:31,980
Let me tell you,

109
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:34,330
Gu Nian's classmates and friends

110
00:05:34,330 --> 00:05:35,750
have all ridden on her motorcycle.

111
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:37,210
She's never let me ride with her.

112
00:05:37,450 --> 00:05:39,290
What I want is for us

113
00:05:39,290 --> 00:05:40,900
both to have our own motorcycles

114
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:42,260
and ride together.

115
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,290
Alright.

116
00:05:45,650 --> 00:05:48,010
Then you should get a motorcycle driver's license. I'll teach you.

117
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,190
[Yin]

118
00:06:23,770 --> 00:06:24,560
Mr. Liu,

119
00:06:25,610 --> 00:06:27,010
please have some water to calm down.

120
00:06:36,650 --> 00:06:38,810
Su Yin, why are you so late?

121
00:06:39,220 --> 00:06:41,050
I'm waiting for your explanation.

122
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:44,490
I'm sorry, Mr. Liu.

123
00:06:45,090 --> 00:06:46,610
This is indeed my fault.

124
00:06:46,970 --> 00:06:48,210
I'll take responsibility for all the consequences.

125
00:06:48,210 --> 00:06:49,170
You'll take responsibility?

126
00:06:49,930 --> 00:06:50,850
How are you going to take responsibility?

127
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:54,490
Mr. Li has always been a very punctual person.

128
00:06:54,570 --> 00:06:55,570
Don't you know that?

129
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:57,530
You were late for nearly an hour.

130
00:06:57,530 --> 00:06:58,610
Do you think he would wait for you?

131
00:06:58,770 --> 00:06:59,810
Who do you think you are?

132
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,550
Today is the first test of the Revisit Project.

133
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:08,890
Such an important matter,

134
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:11,290
and you were actually late?

135
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,010
I trusted you so much before.

136
00:07:14,420 --> 00:07:16,450
I even entrusted the whole project team to you.

137
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:17,530
And what did you do?

138
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:20,170
You were late at a critical moment.

139
00:07:22,130 --> 00:07:23,610
You've really disappointed me.

140
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,530
Mr. Liu, please be careful.

141
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:36,490
Jiang,

142
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:38,450
why didn't you give the speech on my behalf first?

143
00:07:38,450 --> 00:07:39,570
You could've at least bought me some time.

144
00:07:39,650 --> 00:07:40,810
I did.

145
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,970
I've been slowing the speech down.

146
00:07:42,970 --> 00:07:44,730
The problem is I couldn't hold on anymore.

147
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:47,220
Mr. Li was watching his watch,

148
00:07:47,220 --> 00:07:48,409
sighing,

149
00:07:48,409 --> 00:07:49,610
and listening to me.

150
00:07:49,810 --> 00:07:51,250
He wanted to hear it from you,

151
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:52,620
not from me.

152
00:07:53,450 --> 00:07:55,409
Come on, where did you go?

153
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,250
Today...

154
00:07:58,340 --> 00:07:59,980
is my dad's death anniversary.

155
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:08,800
Anyway, you need to think about how to make up for it.

156
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:55,370
Mom, where is the household registration book?

157
00:08:57,450 --> 00:08:59,620
It's in the drawer.

158
00:09:00,090 --> 00:09:01,820
I've been looking for it in there, but I couldn't find it.

159
00:09:02,810 --> 00:09:03,810
Where else could it be?

160
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:04,650
It's always been there.

161
00:09:04,650 --> 00:09:06,190
You didn't hide it, did you?

162
00:09:06,230 --> 00:09:07,590
Why would I hide it?

163
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:08,980
Well, only you and I know

164
00:09:08,980 --> 00:09:10,450
where the household registration book is.

165
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:11,210
If it's not you,

166
00:09:11,210 --> 00:09:12,170
could it be me?

167
00:09:12,380 --> 00:09:13,850
What do you need the household registration book for?

168
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:17,220
I need it for something.

169
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:19,850
Are you looking for the household registration book

170
00:09:20,610 --> 00:09:21,860
to register your marriage with Feng?

171
00:09:23,030 --> 00:09:23,640
Yes.

172
00:09:27,170 --> 00:09:27,810
Nian,

173
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:29,970
do you know what today is?

174
00:09:31,450 --> 00:09:33,440
Today is your dad's death anniversary.

175
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:36,050
And you're actually thinking of getting married?

176
00:09:39,050 --> 00:09:40,780
What? Didn't I set a reminder

177
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:42,860
on my phone of my dad's death anniversary?

178
00:09:42,860 --> 00:09:44,050
Why didn't it remind me?

179
00:09:44,490 --> 00:09:47,330
Do you need a phone reminder of your dad's death anniversary?

180
00:09:47,850 --> 00:09:49,970
Your head is full of Feng Huanan.

181
00:09:50,170 --> 00:09:52,420
Do you even have room for your father in your heart anymore?

182
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,770
Mom, don't say that.

183
00:09:55,650 --> 00:09:57,650
I know it's my fault about Dad.

184
00:09:57,810 --> 00:09:59,210
I'll go apologize to him tomorrow.

185
00:09:59,970 --> 00:10:02,250
But, can you please give me the household registration book first?

186
00:10:02,370 --> 00:10:04,100
I'm telling you, the household registration book isn't with me.

187
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:05,210
Even if it were,

188
00:10:05,490 --> 00:10:06,690
I wouldn't give it to you.

189
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:09,210
Why wouldn't you give it to me?

190
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:11,150
Even the law states marriage is a free choice.

191
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:13,450
Why wouldn't I give it to you?

192
00:10:13,810 --> 00:10:15,410
Because I'm your mother.

193
00:10:16,010 --> 00:10:18,970
I don't want to stand by and watch you make a mistake!

194
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,420
Yes.

195
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:34,690
You are my mother.

196
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:41,190
But I'm not your puppet.

197
00:10:41,710 --> 00:10:42,750
Since I was a child,

198
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,490
whenever I skateboarded or rode motorcycles,

199
00:10:44,490 --> 00:10:45,770
you said I was irresponsible.

200
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:47,410
When I grew up and started looking for a job,

201
00:10:47,410 --> 00:10:48,450
you wanted to arrange one for me.

202
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:49,970
When I have someone I like,

203
00:10:49,970 --> 00:10:50,890
you want to stop me from being with him.

204
00:10:51,170 --> 00:10:53,210
Only when I live the way you want me to,

205
00:10:53,210 --> 00:10:54,180
am I considered the good

206
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:54,940
and obedient child.

207
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:56,530
I know it.

208
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:58,250
I know these years have been tough for you.

209
00:10:58,410 --> 00:11:00,450
I've been compromising myself to please you,

210
00:11:00,690 --> 00:11:02,010
just so you wouldn't be upset.

211
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:04,890
But you can't just think about yourself

212
00:11:04,890 --> 00:11:06,380
and not care about my life, right?

213
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:10,010
What did you say?

214
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:13,980
All these years, you've been pretending to be happy

215
00:11:14,810 --> 00:11:16,850
just to please me?

216
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:17,710
Yes.

217
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:20,410
I've been pretending to be happy.

218
00:11:20,970 --> 00:11:22,370
But now, I don't want to pretend anymore.

219
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:23,820
And I can't keep pretending any longer.

220
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:26,300
Nian, do you know what you just said?

221
00:11:27,930 --> 00:11:29,050
I know exactly what I said.

222
00:11:31,490 --> 00:11:33,410
Because you've never understood the real me.

223
00:11:34,090 --> 00:11:35,690
Why do I like Feng Huanan?

224
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:39,120
Because in front of him, I don't have to pretend,

225
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:41,050
and I don't have to be so perfect.

226
00:11:41,370 --> 00:11:43,650
The love he gives me is equal.

227
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:45,490
Mom,

228
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:49,450
I've never felt unconditional love

229
00:11:49,450 --> 00:11:50,650
from you,

230
00:11:50,650 --> 00:11:53,010
nor have I ever been my true self!

231
00:11:57,810 --> 00:11:58,980
No matter what you say,

232
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:01,650
even if you don't give me the household registration book,

233
00:12:01,650 --> 00:12:03,200
I will still get married.

234
00:12:03,610 --> 00:12:04,770
I want you to know

235
00:12:04,970 --> 00:12:06,600
that we won't be defeated by reality,

236
00:12:07,190 --> 00:12:08,120
and that my life

237
00:12:08,890 --> 00:12:10,810
will no longer be controlled by anyone.

238
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:13,800
Gu Nian!

239
00:12:24,330 --> 00:12:24,980
Gu Nian.

240
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:43,910
Mom? Mom!

241
00:12:44,890 --> 00:12:46,620
Mom, hang in there.

242
00:12:46,620 --> 00:12:48,290
I'll call Gu Nian and ask her to come back.

243
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:50,070
Don't call her.

244
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,550
I don't want to see her.

245
00:12:52,090 --> 00:12:52,880
Okay.

246
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:54,490
Get up first.

247
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:55,980
Come on.

248
00:12:59,970 --> 00:13:00,820
Let's go to the hospital first.

249
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,010
Ambulance!

250
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:35,920
Lin Xi.

251
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:36,820
It's okay.

252
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:37,600
Don't worry.

253
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:39,570
I've already asked the attending doctor.

254
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,960
It's a mild cerebrovascular blockage.

255
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:42,610
They've already done thrombolysis treatment.

256
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:44,070
She's temporarily out of danger now.

257
00:13:44,570 --> 00:13:45,820
Aunt Dai has woken up.

258
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:46,700
The treatment was timely,

259
00:13:47,010 --> 00:13:48,610
so there shouldn't be any serious long-term effects.

260
00:13:48,690 --> 00:13:50,010
But the MRI shows that

261
00:13:50,010 --> 00:13:51,570
there are still several areas in her blood vessels that are narrowed.

262
00:13:51,890 --> 00:13:54,050
Lin Xi, you must help me

263
00:13:54,350 --> 00:13:55,820
find the most authoritative doctor in this field.

264
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:57,170
Money is no object.

265
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:58,320
We must cure my mother.

266
00:13:58,570 --> 00:13:59,810
You don't need to tell me that.

267
00:14:00,210 --> 00:14:01,090
She's not only your mother;

268
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,250
she's also my Aunt Dai.

269
00:14:02,930 --> 00:14:04,680
Don't worry, I'll do my best.

270
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:06,540
Come on, let's sit down and talk.

271
00:14:07,690 --> 00:14:08,610
Try to relax a bit.

272
00:14:11,770 --> 00:14:12,680
What about that Gu Nian?

273
00:14:13,170 --> 00:14:14,100
Why didn't I see her?

274
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:15,860
My mom said she didn't want to see her

275
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,210
and told me not to contact her.

276
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:19,010
Wait, what exactly did she do

277
00:14:19,010 --> 00:14:20,210
to make Aunt Dai so angry?

